A man has died in a serious road traffic accident. Man dies in crash in King's Park area A man has died in a serious road traffic accident.Carmunnock Road, on the fringes of King's Park in Glasgow's south side, was closed to traffic after the incident between Croftpark Avenue and Croftfoot Road from around 8.30pm last night.The road reopened at about 2.30am.Police did not immediately provide any more details of the victim or the accident. 